# Docker Directory Structure

Base location for container **data** on this host. Compose files are **not**
stored here — services are deployed by **Komodo** (see below). This directory
holds only persistent application data plus host-managed scaffolding.

## Layout

```text
{{ common_docker_dir }}/
├── README.md          # This file (managed by the common_docker Ansible role)
└── appdata/           # Persistent per-service data (bind-mount target)
    ├── {service-1}/   # e.g. adguard-1/, technitium-1/, paperless-ngx/
    ├── {service-2}/
    └── ...
```

Services that use Docker **named volumes** instead of bind mounts (e.g. patchmon,
omni) may have no `appdata/` entry — their data lives under
`/var/lib/docker/volumes/`.

> Compose files do not live under `{{ common_docker_dir }}/<service>/`; Komodo
> deploys them from a git checkout under `/etc/komodo/` — see Deployment.

## Deployment (Komodo)

Services are deployed by the **Komodo Periphery** agent, not from this directory:

- **Source of truth**: `services/<service>/docker-compose.yml` in the
  `proxmox-infra` git repo (GitLab).
- **On push to `main`**: a GitLab webhook triggers Komodo Core, which syncs
  `komodo/*.toml` and has the target host's Periphery run `docker compose up -d`
  from a git checkout under `/etc/komodo/` (never `{{ common_docker_dir }}`).
- **Custom images** (e.g. unbound) are built and signed by GitLab CI.

Responsibilities on this host:

- **Komodo** manages compose deployment from `/etc/komodo/`.
- **Ansible (`common_docker`)** manages: Docker install, this base directory,
  the backup directory (`{{ common_docker_backup_dir }}`), and this README.
- **`appdata/<service>/`** is created at deploy time by the service/Komodo.

## Volumes & environment

Compose files reference data via the `${APPDATA_DIR}` variable
(= `{{ common_docker_dir }}/appdata`):

```yaml
services:
  app:
    image: registry.example/app:1.2.3
    volumes:
      - ${APPDATA_DIR}/{service}/data:/app/data
    environment:
      - TZ=${TZ}
```

Non-secret values come from `komodo/variables.toml`; secrets are rendered from
Ansible Vault into the host's Periphery `[secrets]` — never committed `.env`
files.

## Local operations

To act on a service on this host (restart, logs, recreate), use the `dc*`
helpers in `~/.docker_aliases` — they resolve the **Komodo-deployed** stack
automatically (correct compose file + env). Do **not** recreate the old
`{{ common_docker_dir }}/<service>/` directory or run `docker compose` from here.

## Notes

- Docker daemon runs as root; containers are managed by user `{{ user }}`
  (member of the `docker` group).
- `{{ common_docker_dir }}/` is owned by `{{ user }}:docker`; follows the FHS
  convention that `/srv` holds site-specific data.
